  "local_port": 43402,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "My car back glass has been broken, how can I claim United India insurance?",
  "response": "I'm sorry to hear about the damage to your car's back glass. To file a claim with **United India Insurance**, follow these steps to ensure a smooth and efficient process:\n\n### **1. Review Your Insurance Policy**\n\nBefore initiating a claim, verify that your motor insurance policy with United India Insurance covers glass damage. Glass coverage is often included as an add-on or under specific plan features such as \"Zebra\" or \"Zero Depreciation.\" Ensure that:\n- **Comprehensive Coverage:** Your policy includes glass breakage or windshield coverage.\n- **No-Claim Bonus (NCB) Impact:** Check if filing a glass claim affects your NCB.\n\n### **2. Report the Incident Promptly**\n\n- **Time Frame:** It's crucial to report the damage as soon as possible. Delayed reporting can complicate the claim process.\n- **Contact Methods:**\n  - **Phone:** Call United India Insurance's customer service at their helpline number (you can find this on your policy documents or their official website).\n  - **Online:** Visit the [United India Insurance official website](https://www.unitedindia.com/) and navigate to the 'Claim' section to initiate an online claim.\n  - **Branch Visit:** Alternatively, visit the nearest United India Insurance branch office to report the claim in person.\n\n### **3. Gather Necessary Documentation**\n\nPrepare the following documents to support your claim:\n- **Completed Claim Form:** Available on the United India Insurance website or at their branch offices.\n- **Policy Document:** A copy of your motor insurance policy.\n- **Vehicle Registration Certificate (RC):** Proof of vehicle ownership.\n- **Driving License:** A copy for identity verification.\n- **Photographs:** Clear images of the damaged back glass and surrounding areas.\n- **FIR/Police Report:** If the damage resulted from theft, vandalism, or an accident, obtain a First Information Report from the local police station.\n- **Repair Estimates:** Obtain quotes from authorized repair centers if required.\n\n### **4. Submit Your Claim**\n\n- **Online Submission:** Use the insurer\u2019s online portal to upload scanned copies of the required documents.\n- **In-Person Submission:** Visit a United India Insurance branch with all the necessary documents and submit your claim directly to a representative.\n\n### **5. Claim Assessment**\n\nAfter submission:\n- **Assessment Team Visit:** An insurance assessor may visit your location to inspect the damage.\n- **Approval Process:** The assessor will evaluate the extent of the damage and verify the authenticity of the claim.\n- **Communication:** Stay in touch with the claims representative for updates and any additional information that might be required.\n\n### **6. Repair and Settlement**\n\n- **Authorized Repair Centers:** United India Insurance may have tie-ups with specific repair centers. It's advisable to use these to facilitate smoother claim processing.\n- **Direct Settlement:** Once approved, the insurer will either arrange for the repair directly or reimburse you based on the policy terms after you complete the repair at your chosen workshop.\n- **Deductible Amount:** Be aware of any applicable deductibles as per your policy, which you might need to pay out-of-pocket.\n\n### **7. Follow-Up**\n\n- **Track Your Claim:** Use the claim reference number provided to monitor the status of your claim through the insurer\u2019s website or customer service.\n- **Customer Support:** If you face any delays or issues, contact United India Insurance\u2019s customer support for assistance.\n\n### **Additional Tips**\n\n- **Maintain Copies:** Keep copies of all submitted documents and correspondence related to your claim.\n- **Timeliness:** Prompt action can expedite the claim process and reduce potential complications.\n- **Understand Your Policy:** Familiarize yourself with the terms and conditions related to glass coverage to avoid surprises during the settlement.\n\n### **Contact Information**\n\n- **Official Website:** [www.unitedindia.com](https://www.unitedindia.com/)\n- **Customer Care Phone Number:** You can find the latest contact numbers on the official website or your policy documents.\n- **Email Support:** Reach out through the contact emails provided on their website for specific inquiries.\n\nBy following these steps and ensuring you have all required documentation, you can effectively file and process your glass breakage claim with United India Insurance. If you have any specific questions or encounter issues during the process, contacting their customer support directly will provide personalized assistance.",
